    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-08-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-08-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="457"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d457">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 1229/6.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Italian Chargé</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-08-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 23, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Chargé</hi>: In reply to your note of the 19th
                    instant, I beg to inclose for the information of your Government copies of the
                    correspondence between this department and the British embassy in regard to the
                    renunciation of extraterritorial jurisdiction of the United States in
                    Zanzibar.</p>
                <p>A copy of the treaty of February 25, 1905, between the United States and
                    Zanzibar, is also inclosed.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
